Taking the pressure off type 2 diabetes mellitus: implementing hypertension 
guidelines.

Grubbs RS(1), Sica DA.

Author information:
(1)Division of Nephrology, Virginia Commonwealth University Health System, 
Richmond, VA, USA. grubbsr@vcu.edu

Successful treatment of hypertension in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus 
increases life expectancy and reduces the risk of many of the complications 
associated with diabetes, such as heart disease, stroke, and retinopathy. 
Controlling blood pressure also protects against advancing renal disease, with 
several recent studies having clearly shown the advantage of 
